foliation.note: Numbering in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the first leaf recto of each quire, possibly by M.R. James. Full foliation added after digitisation.

collation.p:
The manuscript comprises sixteen quires composed of eight leaves. There are leaves missing in quires 9 and 11.
Quire 18 (ff. 1-8)
Quire 28 (ff. 9-16)
Quire 38 (ff. 17-24)
Quire 48 (ff. 25-32)
Quire 58 (ff. 33-40)
Quire 68 (ff. 41-48)
Quire 78 (ff. 49-56)
Quire 88 (ff. 57-64)
Quire 98-1 (ff. 65-71: seventh leaf missing)
Quire 108 (ff. 72-79)
Quire 118-1 (ff. 80-86: fifth leaf missing)
Quire 128 (ff. 87-94)
Quire 138 (ff. 95-102)
Quire 148 (ff. 103-110)
Quire 158 (ff. 111-118)
Quire 168 (ff. 119-125: f. 126 used as rear pastedown)

p.signatures: Quires 1-9 signed on last verso with a bold roman numeral; quire 14 signed 'IIII'.

p.catchwords: Catchwords at the end of quires 1-2 and 5-8; all except quire 8 mostly trimmed.

layout.seg: Two columns, 36 lines, frame and lines ruled in leadpoint. Pricked in both margins. Written above top line.

decoNote.p: Red and green arabesque initial on plain parchment ground (N, 12 ll., f. 1r); red and plain parchment abstract-patterned initial (I, 15 ll., f. 95r).
Green initial (M, 2 ll., f. 75v) and red initial (Q, 3 ll., f. 76r) with minimal flourishing of dots and wavy lines in red.
Plain initials in red, green or blue (e.g. S, 8 ll., f. 25v; D, 8 ll., f. 54v; S, 4 ll., f. 100r).
1-line initials in ink of text set into the left margin, some with arabesque decoration (e.g. f. 103r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Extensions of letters into the bottom margin, with two turning into a bow and arrow (ff. 10r, 31v) and one accompanied by a dog (f. 18r).

note.p: Some passages appear to have been erased and corrected (e.g. ff. 13r, 30r, 76r).
Marginalia in a contemporary hand throughout (e.g. ff. 4v, 12r, 30r, 35v, 36r, 81v, 91r, 115v).
Notes in a 15th-century cursive hand throughout (e.g. 5r, 29v, 78r, 86r, 101r).
Brackets and nota marks throughout; pencil marks throughout, including majuscule R, and manicules in pencil from f. 87r onward.

Titles written on front pastedown in a 14th-century hand hand for De officiis and in a 17th-century hand for the others. Titles are also inscribed in the same 17th-century hand at the beginning of each work.

binding.p: Original alum-tawed skin over wooden boards, sewn on two bands slightly raised on the flat spine. Mark of a clasp on front cover and of a pin in the centre of the back cover. At the foot of the back cover is a circular hole surrounded by four bronze nails, possibly from a chain-staple, but unusual if so.

history.acquisition: Given to Queens' College Library in the early 1630s by Francis Tyndall Tyndall, Francis with a 17th-century inscription recording the gift on front pastedown: 'Donum Francisci Tyndall armigeri'.

recordHist.source: This catalogue entry draws on the description in M.R. James, A descriptive catalogue of the western manuscripts in the library of Queens' College, Cambridge (Cambridge, 1905), and R.M. Thomson's catalogue of the medieval manuscripts of Queens' College (forthcoming).

availability.p: For further information on the availability of the manuscript, please contact Queens' Old Library and Special Collections.
